              <harm staff="1" tstamp="3">②m</harm>
            </measure>

          </section>
        </score>
      </mdiv>
    </body>
  </music>
</mei>

<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- D major, 12 measures. Tonal center somewhat ambiguous (many Bm arrivals → feels like vi minor).
- I (D): D2-A2-D3-F#3 "334" — solid foundation
- ii (Em): E2-B2-E3-G3 — open P5 bass
- iii (F#m): F#2-C#3-F#3-A3 — both sharps active; heavier register
- IV (G): G2-D3-G3-B3 — warm IV, substituted for non-diatonic Bb throughout
- V (A): A2-E3-A3-C#4 — full V with 3rd
- vi (Bm): B2-F#3-B3-D4 — minor vi, acts as tonic in later measures
- vii° (C#°): C#3-E3-G3 lighter dim triad
- viiø7: C#3-E3-G3-B3 "333" — half-dim for color

Bb substitution rationale: Bb appears as a chromatic upper neighbor in m9-12.
The underlying harmonic function is neighbor to Bm (b6 coloring) → substituted
with IV (G major) which shares two tones with Bm (B and D) and feels similar.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- m1: LH G→B (P3 inner voice) while bass B2→G2 descent.
- m7-8: Bm→F#m inner voice motion D4→C#4 (half step, characteristic minor color).
- m9-12: C#→B→A (descending chromatic line in melody mirrors vi→vii°→vi in harmony).
- Final Bm: all voices resolve inward, LH sustains full Bm voicing.

TEXTURE ARC:
- m1-4: Four-on-the-floor chord changes, 2+3 notes, establishing ii/iii/IV/I motion.
- m5-8: V dominant tension → release to I, iii–vi–vii° color.
- m9-12: Upper register (C5-D5 melody), richer 3+4 note texture, Bm tonal area.
  Climax at m9-10 with D5/C5, converges to Bm final in m11-12.
-->
